### Description

I'm trying set some zone flags by Angular guide to disable requestAnimationFrame and timers patch.

https://angular.io/guide/zone#setting-up-zonejs

```typescript
(window as any).__Zone_disable_requestAnimationFrame = true;
(window as any).__Zone_disable_timers = true;
import 'zone.js';
```

In the component, I have added following code:

```typescript
  ngAfterViewInit() {
    setTimeout(() => {
      this.value1 = 1;
    }, 1000);

    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      this.value2 = 2;
    });
  }
```

Update field data in `setTimeout` and `requestAnimationFrame` should not trigger change detection.

But updated `value1` and `value2` still are displayed on screen.

